summary: This is a standard Office of the Inspector General (OIG) form used to document warnings and assurances provided to a voluntary employee interviewee. It indicates an OIG investigation is being conducted, but the specific subject of the investigation is redacted. The form includes a waiver section for the employee to sign, acknowledging the voluntary nature of the interview.
keyFacts: The document is an OIG Form III-226/2, used for non-custodial/employee interviews.
It confirms an Office of the Inspector General investigation was being conducted, but the subject of the investigation is fully redacted.
The form outlines the voluntary nature of the interview and the potential use of statements in future proceedings.
The date, time, place, and the interviewee's name are all redacted on the form.
